The employees, who innate pro-Palestina choirs, and wore the traditional Arab headdresses, also used the social X and Twitch to post images and document with direct videos their protest.
The activists, gathered in a group called "No Tech for Apartheid", read some statements in which they accuse Google of doing business with those who "carry forward the genocide", bombing the Gaza Strip, and asked to cancel its participation in the "Nimbus Project", a $1.2 billion deal that involves Google Cloud and Amazon Web Services. Another group has occupied the tenth floor of Google's headquarters in Manhattan.&nbsp;

